x10.matrix.dist.summa

Class SummaSparseMultDense

  • x10.lang.Object
    • x10.matrix.dist.summa.SummaSparseMultDense

  • public class SummaSparseMultDense
extends x10.lang.Object
    This class implements matrix multiplication between distributed sparse and distributed dense matrix using SUMMA algorithm. The results are stored distributed dense matrices.

        Perform SUMMA distributed matrix multiply: C = A * B + beta * C.
        Parameters:
        ps - panel size
        beta - scaling factor for output matrix
        A - first input distributed sparse matrix in multiplication
        B - second input distributed dense matrix in multiplication
        C - the input/result distributed dense matrix
        See Also:
        parallelMult(wk1, wk2), SummaDense.parallelMult(wk1, wk2)
